The function of the IAASA is to supervise the regulation by the accountancy bodies of their members. IAASA has a wide range of oversight functions in relation to accountancy bodies including the power to


•Intervene in the disciplinary processes of the accountancy bodies where it deems it necessary;


•Carry out independent investigations of possible breaches of standards of prescribed accountancy bodies by their members;


•Require accountancy bodies to amend their rules and their disciplinary and investigation procedures;


•Grant recognition to bodies of accountants under the Companies Acts; and 


•Review the accounts of certain categories of companies and apply to the courts to compel directors of a company to amend accounts that are not in compliance with the Companies Acts. This function has yet to be commenced.

